text: Park Jung-yeon (born 13 May 1997) is a South Korean actress and model. She made her acting debut in the last episode of tvN's drama Hi Bye, Mama! as the adult Cho Seo-woo and acted her first regular role in TV Chosun's Kingmaker: The Change of Destiny as the future Empress Myeongseong. ==Personal life== She is a former trainee of SM Entertainment and was a former member of SM Rookies. In 2019 she left SM and signed with KeyEast to become an actress.
